<subSubSection id="72E8EC78D025530949239881E88D5C4A" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="C5858FE562CEA369D4C92F651B322248" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8CE614486C6A600FEA29B123B7FC3D9E" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">
A relatively uncommon species found principally in semi-arid regions in the central and northern regions of Chile and adjacent areas of Bolivia, found on sandy soil or soil over rock, often near streams. The species is characterized by its dioicous sexual condition, evenly foliate stems, large narrowly ovate leaves that are spirally twisted around the stem when dry, a weak limbidium distally, and brown to red-brown rhizoidal tubers. 
<bibRefCitation id="DAD7E90F24EAB283F33F66530DF04286" author="Ochi, H" journalOrPublisher="Nature and Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="49 - 154" refId="B17" refString="Ochi, H, 1980. A revision of the Neotropical Bryoideae, Musci (First Part). Journal of the Faculty of Education, Tottori University. Nature and Science 29: 49 - 154" title="A revision of the Neotropical Bryoideae, Musci (First Part). Journal of the Faculty of Education, Tottori University." volume="29" year="1980">Ochi (1980)</bibRefCitation>
had synonymized it with 
<taxonomicName id="D2B193FCD638DCFE2BB2622589FD1A18" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. canariense" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="canariense">
<emphasis id="5F4487FD83A1A202420ECAF3A27E63AE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">R. canariense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but it is treated here as a good species (see below under 
<taxonomicName id="81DCCCF98BFDD9F9E52E52D42351F03D" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. canariense" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="canariense">
<emphasis id="E19F4A4D9BABB05868A3F398BB19D20F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">R. canariense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). (Illustration: 
<bibRefCitation id="E7F3C188735B5D8451EBA664D3C499B1" author="Ochi, H" journalOrPublisher="Nature and Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="49 - 154" refId="B17" refString="Ochi, H, 1980. A revision of the Neotropical Bryoideae, Musci (First Part). Journal of the Faculty of Education, Tottori University. Nature and Science 29: 49 - 154" title="A revision of the Neotropical Bryoideae, Musci (First Part). Journal of the Faculty of Education, Tottori University." volume="29" year="1980">Ochi 1980</bibRefCitation>
: 148, as 
<taxonomicName id="B374049C34945126035FE0114DF2E45C" authorityName="Bridel" authorityYear="1817" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Bryum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bryum canariense" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="canariense">
<emphasis id="DAAB48288A30225DD309D7638E3E7E20" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Bryum canariense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
